comments.body:
just waiting isn't enough... we need to make sure the token actually gets renewed.

you can do this like this:

```
if inErr := testClientBuilder(dymClient, ns, saName); inErr != nil {
	t.Fatalf("dynamic get resources failed: %v", inErr)
}
... delete the service account, invalidating the token ...
time.Sleep(time.Second * 10)
if inErr := testClientBuilder(dymClient, ns, saName); inErr != nil {
	t.Fatalf("dynamic get resources failed: %v", inErr)
}
```

